19
00:00:18,564 --> 00:00:20,608
<i>Separatist takeover complete!</i>

20
00:00:20,775 --> 00:00:23,152
<i>Another Republic planet has fallen.</i>

21
00:00:23,277 --> 00:00:26,906
<i>Onderon has seceded to the
Confederacy of Independent Systems</i>

22
00:00:27,073 --> 00:00:29,116
<i>under the rule of a new king.</i>

23
00:00:29,408 --> 00:00:32,119
<i>However, a small band of rebels
have taken refuge</i>

24
00:00:32,245 --> 00:00:35,331
<i>deep within its vast and savage wilderness.</i>

25
00:00:35,456 --> 00:00:36,749
<i>From an abandoned outpost,</i>

26
00:00:36,791 --> 00:00:40,419
<i>they plot to take back the heavily fortified
capital city of Iziz</i>

27
00:00:40,586 --> 00:00:42,922
<i>and end the Separatist occupation.</i>

28
00:00:46,425 --> 00:00:49,095
<i>Unfortunately, the only way
to reclaim Onderon</i>

29
00:00:49,136 --> 00:00:50,763
<i>will be through armed struggle.</i>

30
00:00:51,264 --> 00:00:53,349
<i>But we lack
sufficient hardware and supplies.</i>

31
00:00:53,474 --> 00:00:57,603
Onderon is in your king's rule,
and at the outbreak of the Clone War,

32
00:00:57,770 --> 00:00:59,981
he chose to align it with the Separatists.

33
00:01:00,106 --> 00:01:01,941
<i>Our true king has been silenced.</i>

34
00:01:01,983 --> 00:01:05,987
<i>The one you recognize
is a traitor and a Separatist minion.</i>

35
00:01:06,153 --> 00:01:07,905
<i>We need your help to survive this.</i>

36
00:01:08,656 --> 00:01:11,492
Find a way we shall.

37
00:01:11,867 --> 00:01:13,869
<i>We await your answer.</i>

38
00:01:18,708 --> 00:01:22,211
There are pockets of rebels on many
of these planets that just need guidance.

39
00:01:22,378 --> 00:01:26,382
With training and resources,
they could attack soft targets

40
00:01:26,507 --> 00:01:29,343
while the Republic continues
to engage them on the battlefield.

41
00:01:29,427 --> 00:01:31,846
That sounds like terrorism, Anakin.

42
00:01:31,887 --> 00:01:33,681
Well, I think of it as an insurgency.

43
00:01:33,764 --> 00:01:36,559
To help realign these planets
with the Republic.

44
00:01:36,767 --> 00:01:41,105
We can divide the Separatist forces
and press them on two fronts.

45
00:01:41,355 --> 00:01:44,525
A means to an end fear cannot be.

46
00:01:45,276 --> 00:01:48,446
Stop those who spread terror
the Jedi must.

47
00:01:48,863 --> 00:01:52,867
Indeed. What you're suggesting
would open up dangerous possibilities.

48
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:55,036
We must not train terrorists.

49
00:01:55,286 --> 00:01:56,579
Uh, rebels.

50
00:01:56,954 --> 00:02:00,374
How we conduct war is
what distinguishes us from others.

51
00:02:00,458 --> 00:02:02,710
Funding rebels to overthrow
a legitimate government

52
00:02:02,752 --> 00:02:04,795
puts innocent lives at risk.

53
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:08,466
We can minimize collateral damage
by using arms that mainly affect droids.

54
00:02:09,091 --> 00:02:11,385
The least we can do
is help them defend themselves.

55
00:02:11,761 --> 00:02:13,554
Test the tactic while we're at it.

56
00:02:14,805 --> 00:02:16,974
This could be a great new weapon for us.

57
00:02:21,062 --> 00:02:22,313
Hmm.

58
00:02:22,396 --> 00:02:24,565
Train and observe.

59
00:02:24,607 --> 00:02:26,734
Send advisors we will.

60
00:02:26,776 --> 00:02:28,402
I'll assemble a team.

61
00:02:28,819 --> 00:02:30,655
I'm going with you.

62
00:02:30,738 --> 00:02:32,490
What? You don't trust me?

63
00:02:32,740 --> 00:02:35,326
Too much. That's what worries me.

64
00:02:49,965 --> 00:02:52,927
<i>This is Valkyrie 29-29.
We're coming up on the drop zone.</i>

65
00:02:59,350 --> 00:03:00,810
Go! Go! Go! Go!

66
00:03:26,627 --> 00:03:28,212
We've spotted them, sir.

67
00:03:39,140 --> 00:03:40,182
Stay where you are.

68
00:03:44,812 --> 00:03:46,564
Identify yourselves.

69
00:03:50,234 --> 00:03:52,236
It's all right. We're friends.

70
00:03:52,570 --> 00:03:54,196
Jedi.

71
00:03:57,950 --> 00:04:01,662
I'm Commander Tano. We're here
to help you take back your planet.

72
00:04:02,413 --> 00:04:05,958
My name is Steela.
I'll guide you to our secret base.

73
00:05:13,067 --> 00:05:14,235
Hmm?

74
00:05:17,029 --> 00:05:18,072
Mmm.

75
00:05:18,155 --> 00:05:20,574
A bit rough around the edges,
wouldn't you say?

76
00:05:20,991 --> 00:05:22,743
That's why I brought Rex here.

77
00:05:22,827 --> 00:05:26,831
They're not exactly what I would call shiny,
sir, but I can work with them.

78
00:05:46,225 --> 00:05:49,436
-General Skywalker.
-At your service.

79
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:53,691
This is General Kenobi, Commander Tano
and Captain Rex.

80
00:05:54,108 --> 00:05:57,528
We're looking forward to taking the fight
to those scrapping droids.

81
00:05:57,736 --> 00:06:00,281
Yes, all in good time.

82
00:06:01,198 --> 00:06:03,367
Saw. Saw Gerrera.

83
00:06:03,576 --> 00:06:07,788
He fashions himself as our leader,
though no one elected him.

84
00:06:08,789 --> 00:06:10,708
Well, for now, we're in charge.

85
00:06:11,125 --> 00:06:12,751
And there is much to learn.

86
00:06:18,632 --> 00:06:20,634
The Separatists have strength in numbers.

87
00:06:20,801 --> 00:06:23,721
We're gonna show you
how to target and destroy them.

88
00:06:23,804 --> 00:06:26,765
Now, to be clear,
we are not here to fight your war.

89
00:06:26,891 --> 00:06:28,976
Rather, to show you how to conduct it

90
00:06:29,059 --> 00:06:31,729
in the most efficient
and successful way possible.

91
00:06:34,815 --> 00:06:36,567
Captain Rex.

92
00:06:37,484 --> 00:06:40,321
I'll show you
how the 501 st destroy clankers.

93
00:06:40,446 --> 00:06:45,117
First, I need volunteers to carry supplies
from our entry point a half-click west.

94
00:06:45,451 --> 00:06:48,078
-Shouldn't be a problem.
-Excellent.

95
00:06:50,915 --> 00:06:53,834
Lux, it's good to see you again.

96
00:06:54,001 --> 00:06:56,003
It's good to see you, too, Ahsoka.

97
00:06:56,295 --> 00:06:59,465
I didn't realize you had
such strong ties to Onderon.

98
00:06:59,632 --> 00:07:03,010
Onderon is my home.
My mother represented it in the Senate.

99
00:07:03,636 --> 00:07:06,764
Your voice is strong. Like hers was.

100
00:07:07,514 --> 00:07:10,309
Have you reconsidered
joining the Republic Senate?

101
00:07:10,476 --> 00:07:14,146
Even if we do take back Onderon,
it won't change how I feel.

102
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:16,148
I'm not fighting for the Republic.

103
00:07:16,523 --> 00:07:19,193
Well, what matters now
is we need each other's help.

104
00:07:19,318 --> 00:07:20,986
Just like we did on Carlac.

105
00:07:21,654 --> 00:07:24,823
Carlac? What happened on Carlac?

106
00:07:26,116 --> 00:07:29,036
Ahsoka is the reason I'm here
and not with Death Watch.

107
00:07:29,495 --> 00:07:32,373
-Really?
-What he means is...

108
00:07:32,456 --> 00:07:34,875
She saved me from a huge mistake.

109
00:07:38,879 --> 00:07:39,964
Hmm...

110
00:07:40,047 --> 00:07:42,341
Lux obviously thinks highly of you.

111
00:07:42,383 --> 00:07:43,550
I guess so.

112
00:07:43,676 --> 00:07:45,844
Let's hope that respect is well founded.

113
00:07:50,349 --> 00:07:53,352
The pilot in the front hatch
controls the tank, the shells

114
00:07:53,394 --> 00:07:55,229
and the short-range blasters.

115
00:07:55,312 --> 00:07:58,732
The commander in the top hatch
controls the turret and the main cannon.

116
00:07:59,024 --> 00:08:03,320
You have to take out both chambers,
otherwise the tank will remain operational.

117
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:25,259
Everyone, divide up into teams of two, and
we'll practice an assault on both hatches.

118
00:08:26,719 --> 00:08:28,262
I'll take the top.

119
00:08:28,345 --> 00:08:30,097
Let's see what you're made of, Bonteri.

120
00:08:44,069 --> 00:08:45,446
Sorry about that.

121
00:08:46,697 --> 00:08:48,699
You're a terrible soldier, Bonteri.

122
00:08:50,117 --> 00:08:54,079
I'm not sure if they're more interested
in fighting the droids or each other.

123
00:08:54,246 --> 00:08:57,458
They'll learn.
We just need time to train them properly.

124
00:08:57,583 --> 00:08:59,293
Keep your eyes on the quick learners.

125
00:08:59,626 --> 00:09:02,129
-In this fight, time is not on our side.
-Come on ! Hustle!

126
00:09:02,254 --> 00:09:03,881
Go, go, go, go, go!

127
00:09:28,906 --> 00:09:32,326
An unscheduled ship entered the
atmosphere in sector S-11

128
00:09:32,451 --> 00:09:34,161
and failed to register.

129
00:09:34,244 --> 00:09:36,914
The rebels may be operating in that area.

130
00:09:37,289 --> 00:09:38,916
Check it out.

131
00:09:45,631 --> 00:09:49,468
Come on, move it like a soldier!
Like a real soldier!

132
00:09:49,510 --> 00:09:51,512
Come on, Donald ! Pick it up, Hutch!

133
00:09:51,637 --> 00:09:54,014
- You can do better than that.
- Come on, hustle!

134
00:09:54,264 --> 00:09:55,849
I said hustle!

135
00:09:56,016 --> 00:09:59,770
That's what I'm talking about right there.
Go, go, go! Good. Good!

136
00:10:00,020 --> 00:10:01,688
-You sure you're up for this?
-Saw...

137
00:10:01,814 --> 00:10:04,858
-It was an accident.
-You would have had us both killed.

138
00:10:06,944 --> 00:10:07,986
Just stop it.

139
00:10:09,488 --> 00:10:12,199
Sit down, boy, this isn't the Senate.

140
00:10:12,324 --> 00:10:13,867
You've got no talent for this.

141
00:10:13,951 --> 00:10:17,329
It's going to take a lot more than muscle
to defeat the Separatists.

142
00:10:17,788 --> 00:10:20,666
Politics have failed us. We have no choice.

143
00:10:21,166 --> 00:10:22,626
We always have a choice.

144
00:10:23,377 --> 00:10:24,878
Then make yours.

145
00:10:25,671 --> 00:10:28,382
Look, if we're going to succeed,
you'll need to be exceptional

146
00:10:28,507 --> 00:10:30,384
with words and action.

147
00:10:30,509 --> 00:10:32,553
There will be time for both.

148
00:10:39,184 --> 00:10:43,147
Destroyers are quick, pack twin blasters
and come with their own shield generators.

149
00:10:43,230 --> 00:10:45,983
Nothing short of a cannon will pierce it.

150
00:10:46,441 --> 00:10:48,610
But they do have two weaknesses,

151
00:10:48,735 --> 00:10:51,238
and you will need to work together
to exploit them.

152
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,411
The shields deflect high-velocity attacks.

153
00:11:02,541 --> 00:11:06,253
What the shields don't stop are slow
or stationary objects.

154
00:11:06,420 --> 00:11:09,798
They're designed to absorb them
so nothing hinders their movement.

155
00:11:17,472 --> 00:11:19,892
Destroyers are blind from behind.

156
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:23,228
A distraction combined with a rear assault
will give you a kill.

157
00:11:23,729 --> 00:11:26,565
The trick is to get the right speed
on the droid popper.

158
00:11:29,943 --> 00:11:33,655
These are unarmed. Just concentrate
on getting it past the shield.

159
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,742
Watch and learn.

160
00:11:42,748 --> 00:11:44,082
Quite brilliant.

161
00:11:55,302 --> 00:11:56,970
Hmm. Nice touch.

162
00:11:57,471 --> 00:11:58,931
Thanks.

163
00:12:01,141 --> 00:12:02,517
Not bad.

164
00:12:11,818 --> 00:12:12,945
Ugh.

165
00:12:13,904 --> 00:12:17,449
Be mindful of your frustration,
it will only hold you back.

166
00:12:17,991 --> 00:12:19,826
Here, use your shoulder.

167
00:12:19,952 --> 00:12:22,829
Let your arm swing,
and keep your eyes on the target.

168
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:27,960
Great.

169
00:12:28,168 --> 00:12:29,836
Okay, let's get back to work.

170
00:12:29,962 --> 00:12:32,631
Everyone pair up. We'll practice in groups.

171
00:12:38,136 --> 00:12:41,431
Hey, Commander,
how about, uh, helping me practice?

172
00:12:58,991 --> 00:13:01,201
Roger, roger. This is Command.

173
00:13:02,035 --> 00:13:04,830
Copy that. I'll send a squad out now.

174
00:13:06,290 --> 00:13:09,876
We've located the rebels.
Proceed to sector S-29.

175
00:13:10,419 --> 00:13:11,628
Shoot to kill.

176
00:13:33,483 --> 00:13:36,028
I can't get the distance or the speed right.

177
00:13:36,111 --> 00:13:39,906
Don't give up. Learning this could save
your life and those around you.

178
00:13:41,950 --> 00:13:43,577
A little backspin might help.

179
00:13:45,329 --> 00:13:47,873
Just take it easy. Don't get frustrated.

180
00:13:55,964 --> 00:13:58,467
-You got it.
-Good teacher, Jedi.

181
00:13:59,217 --> 00:14:00,260
Oh!

182
00:14:00,344 --> 00:14:02,804
Just forget it. I'll never learn this.

183
00:14:06,183 --> 00:14:07,768
Uh, keep practicing.

184
00:14:19,863 --> 00:14:22,699
-You made it look easy.
-Wasn't always that way.

185
00:14:23,867 --> 00:14:26,244
Right, the Force. Is that your secret?

186
00:14:26,703 --> 00:14:28,705
No, perseverance.

187
00:14:29,706 --> 00:14:32,876
Look, you'll get the hang of it.
I wouldn't let it get you down.

188
00:14:33,418 --> 00:14:34,920
I'm not feeling down.

189
00:14:36,713 --> 00:14:38,215
I just know what I'm good at.

190
00:14:56,316 --> 00:14:57,359
Impressive.

191
00:14:58,235 --> 00:15:00,028
Most impressive.

192
00:15:00,112 --> 00:15:03,532
Fixed targets are one thing.
How about this?

193
00:15:14,042 --> 00:15:15,252
Nice job.

194
00:15:18,380 --> 00:15:21,550
You've clearly mastered
your ability to focus.

195
00:15:24,302 --> 00:15:26,763
Snips, are you losing focus?

196
00:15:27,097 --> 00:15:29,641
-No, Master.
-Good.

197
00:15:29,724 --> 00:15:32,811
A head shot is the only decisive way
to disable a droid.

198
00:15:33,395 --> 00:15:37,357
They don't need arms, legs, or even bodies
to pass intel to Central Command.

199
00:15:37,858 --> 00:15:39,860
All right. Shoot at will.

200
00:15:42,946 --> 00:15:45,115
Wait a minute, what is that?

201
00:15:47,242 --> 00:15:48,452
Droids!

202
00:15:52,038 --> 00:15:53,081
Take cover!

203
00:16:05,552 --> 00:16:07,304
It appears the training is over.

204
00:16:18,732 --> 00:16:20,775
I'll take the left flank if you take the right.

205
00:16:21,485 --> 00:16:25,989
No, Anakin, we can only protect them.
We cannot fight this war for them.

206
00:16:30,744 --> 00:16:31,828
There are too many.

207
00:16:31,912 --> 00:16:35,624
But Anakin, Ahsoka and I can hold them off
while you get your people out of here.

208
00:16:38,084 --> 00:16:39,920
You didn't teach us to run.

209
00:16:40,003 --> 00:16:42,380
Saw, use your disrupters
to take out the droids.

210
00:16:42,506 --> 00:16:43,757
I'm on it.

211
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:46,176
Ready, disrupters, on my mark.

212
00:16:47,719 --> 00:16:48,762
Now!

213
00:16:50,514 --> 00:16:51,556
What is that?

214
00:16:52,682 --> 00:16:55,143
-It looks like an explosive.
-How can you tell?

215
00:16:56,728 --> 00:16:59,564
-Not bad.
-That is only the first wave.

216
00:17:12,035 --> 00:17:14,663
-We'll handle this.
-No, I will.

217
00:17:15,497 --> 00:17:16,540
Duck!

218
00:17:36,685 --> 00:17:39,479
Hey, Bonteri, you ready to try again?

219
00:17:42,357 --> 00:17:44,693
-Hey! What are you doing?
-What you taught us!

220
00:17:52,117 --> 00:17:54,077
Surrender, rebel.

221
00:17:54,244 --> 00:17:58,415
You will answer for your crimes
against the Separatist Alliance...

222
00:18:13,263 --> 00:18:15,098
We, uh, need to clean you up.

223
00:18:15,557 --> 00:18:19,728
I like it. Now you look more like
a soldier than a politician.

224
00:18:19,853 --> 00:18:23,148
Well, maybe a good politician
needs to get dirty now and then.

225
00:18:31,239 --> 00:18:33,158
Take confidence from this victory.

226
00:18:33,241 --> 00:18:36,411
But rest assured,
there will be more droids coming

227
00:18:36,620 --> 00:18:38,496
now that they know your position.

228
00:18:38,580 --> 00:18:40,832
It doesn't matter, you're ready now.

229
00:18:40,915 --> 00:18:43,501
We are going to take the fight to the droids.

230
00:18:43,585 --> 00:18:46,004
You don't have to hide in the jungle
any longer.

231
00:18:46,087 --> 00:18:49,466
Droids were a bit dim.
More so than I imagined.

232
00:18:49,549 --> 00:18:53,011
They make up for it in numbers.
They're designed to overwhelm.

233
00:18:53,428 --> 00:18:56,264
But they're not designed
to deal with our approach.

234
00:18:56,514 --> 00:18:58,516
We hit them where they least expect it.

235
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,934
And before they realize what happened...

236
00:19:00,101 --> 00:19:02,270
We fade in with the rest of the population.

237
00:19:02,354 --> 00:19:03,855
Exactly.

238
00:19:03,938 --> 00:19:06,775
We need a plan to get inside the city.

239
00:19:07,067 --> 00:19:09,235
I have an idea.

240
00:19:33,843 --> 00:19:36,179
Identification, please.

241
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:43,603
Halt!

242
00:19:44,312 --> 00:19:46,815
What were you doing
outside of the city gates?

243
00:19:47,482 --> 00:19:49,901
Hunting. We've been trekking for days.

244
00:19:51,152 --> 00:19:54,197
Did you register before your excursion?

245
00:19:55,073 --> 00:19:58,952
No, but most of our time is spent
in the bush collecting our traps.

246
00:19:59,035 --> 00:20:00,662
We come to the city to sell.

247
00:20:01,746 --> 00:20:04,374
You can't get thrip larvae like this in Iziz.

248
00:20:04,457 --> 00:20:07,210
Only the biggest trees
on the other side of Onderon.

249
00:20:07,293 --> 00:20:10,672
Hey, listen, we need to deliver
all of this in time for supper.

250
00:20:11,339 --> 00:20:12,424
Hmm.

251
00:20:12,507 --> 00:20:14,008
Are you scanning anything?

252
00:20:14,676 --> 00:20:17,804
It's hard to tell
with so much organic matter.

253
00:20:18,221 --> 00:20:21,307
Come on !
Our merchants are waiting inside.

254
00:20:21,391 --> 00:20:22,976
Can you hurry it up?

255
00:20:23,810 --> 00:20:26,521
-Let them through.
-Roger, roger.

256
00:20:36,698 --> 00:20:37,824
Good plan.

257
00:20:37,907 --> 00:20:40,785
Like Saw said,
those droids are dumber than we thought.

258
00:20:50,128 --> 00:20:53,715
Not a bad start.
But now the hard work begins.

259
00:20:54,299 --> 00:20:56,885
You must find recruits
and choose your targets wisely.

260
00:20:57,343 --> 00:20:59,053
They'll be looking for us.

261
00:20:59,262 --> 00:21:00,638
We should split up.

262
00:21:00,722 --> 00:21:03,433
Regroup after nightfall.
I'll alert our brothers.

263
00:21:07,312 --> 00:21:09,939
We'll make sure you have
the supplies you need.

264
00:21:10,023 --> 00:21:11,900
Rex and I will take care of that.

265
00:21:12,525 --> 00:21:13,568
Good luck.

266
00:21:13,651 --> 00:21:15,111
You, too.

267
00:21:28,750 --> 00:21:30,460
How do you think they'll do?

268
00:21:31,586 --> 00:21:34,464
I have a feeling
we'll be pleasantly surprised.

269
00:21:34,964 --> 00:21:37,550
So you admit our new strategy will work.

270
00:21:37,801 --> 00:21:39,844
I am hopeful, Anakin.

271
00:21:40,428 --> 00:21:41,721
Hopeful.

272
00:21:41,745 --> 00:21:46,745
http://hiqve.com/

